11size_t utf8_to_utf32(const char* buf, size_t len, char32_t* utf32_output) {
12 const uint8_t* data = reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(buf);
13 size_t pos = 0;
14 const char32_t* start{utf32_output};
15 while (pos < len) {
16 // try to convert the next block of 16 ASCII bytes
17 if (pos + 16 <= len) { // if it is safe to read 16 more
18 // bytes, check that they are ascii
19 uint64_t v1;
20 std::memcpy(&v1, data + pos, sizeof(uint64_t));
21 uint64_t v2;
22 std::memcpy(&v2, data + pos + sizeof(uint64_t), sizeof(uint64_t));
23 uint64_t v{v1 | v2};
24 if ((v & 0x8080808080808080) == 0) {
25 size_t final_pos = pos + 16;
26 while (pos < final_pos) {
27 *utf32_output++ = char32_t(buf[pos]);
28 pos++;
29 }
30 continue;
31 }
32 }
33 uint8_t leading_byte = data[pos]; // leading byte
34 if (leading_byte < 0b10000000) {
35 // converting one ASCII byte !!!
36 *utf32_output++ = char32_t(leading_byte);
37 pos++;
38 } else if ((leading_byte & 0b11100000) == 0b11000000) {
39 // We have a two-byte UTF-8
40 if (pos + 1 >= len) {
41 return 0;
42 } // minimal bound checking
43 if ((data[pos + 1] & 0b11000000) != 0b10000000) {
44 return 0;
45 }
46 // range check
47 uint32_t code_point =
48 (leading_byte & 0b00011111) << 6 | (data[pos + 1] & 0b00111111);
49 if (code_point < 0x80 || 0x7ff < code_point) {
50 return 0;
51 }
52 *utf32_output++ = char32_t(code_point);
53 pos += 2;
54 } else if ((leading_byte & 0b11110000) == 0b11100000) {
55 // We have a three-byte UTF-8
56 if (pos + 2 >= len) {
57 return 0;
58 } // minimal bound checking
59
60 if ((data[pos + 1] & 0b11000000) != 0b10000000) {
61 return 0;
62 }
63 if ((data[pos + 2] & 0b11000000) != 0b10000000) {
64 return 0;
65 }
66 // range check
67 uint32_t code_point = (leading_byte & 0b00001111) << 12 |
68 (data[pos + 1] & 0b00111111) << 6 |
69 (data[pos + 2] & 0b00111111);
70 if (code_point < 0x800 || 0xffff < code_point ||
71 (0xd7ff < code_point && code_point < 0xe000)) {
72 return 0;
73 }
74 *utf32_output++ = char32_t(code_point);
75 pos += 3;
76 } else if ((leading_byte & 0b11111000) == 0b11110000) { // 0b11110000
77 // we have a 4-byte UTF-8 word.
78 if (pos + 3 >= len) {
79 return 0;
80 } // minimal bound checking
81 if ((data[pos + 1] & 0b11000000) != 0b10000000) {
82 return 0;
83 }
84 if ((data[pos + 2] & 0b11000000) != 0b10000000) {
85 return 0;
86 }
87 if ((data[pos + 3] & 0b11000000) != 0b10000000) {
88 return 0;
89 }
90
91 // range check
92 uint32_t code_point = (leading_byte & 0b00000111) << 18 |
93 (data[pos + 1] & 0b00111111) << 12 |
94 (data[pos + 2] & 0b00111111) << 6 |
95 (data[pos + 3] & 0b00111111);
96 if (code_point <= 0xffff || 0x10ffff < code_point) {
97 return 0;
98 }
99 *utf32_output++ = char32_t(code_point);
100 pos += 4;
101 } else {
102 return 0;
103 }
104 }
105 return utf32_output - start;
106}

108size_t utf8_length_from_utf32(const char32_t* buf, size_t len) {
109 // We are not BOM aware.
110 const uint32_t* p = reinterpret_cast<const uint32_t*>(buf);
111 size_t counter{0};
112 for (size_t i = 0; i != len; ++i) {
113 ++counter; // ASCII
114 counter += static_cast<size_t>(p[i] > 0x7F); // two-byte
115 counter += static_cast<size_t>(p[i] > 0x7FF); // three-byte
116 counter += static_cast<size_t>(p[i] > 0xFFFF); // four-bytes
117 }
118 return counter;
119}

121size_t utf32_length_from_utf8(const char* buf, size_t len) {
122 const int8_t* p = reinterpret_cast<const int8_t*>(buf);
123 return std::count_if(p, std::next(p, len), [](int8_t c) {
124 // -65 is 0b10111111, anything larger in two-complement's
125 // should start a new code point.
126 return c > -65;
127 });
128}

130size_t utf32_to_utf8(const char32_t* buf, size_t len, char* utf8_output) {
131 const uint32_t* data = reinterpret_cast<const uint32_t*>(buf);
132 size_t pos = 0;
133 const char* start{utf8_output};
134 while (pos < len) {
135 // try to convert the next block of 2 ASCII characters
136 if (pos + 2 <= len) { // if it is safe to read 8 more
137 // bytes, check that they are ascii
138 uint64_t v;
139 std::memcpy(&v, data + pos, sizeof(uint64_t));
140 if ((v & 0xFFFFFF80FFFFFF80) == 0) {
141 *utf8_output++ = char(buf[pos]);
142 *utf8_output++ = char(buf[pos + 1]);
143 pos += 2;
144 continue;
145 }
146 }
147 uint32_t word = data[pos];
148 if ((word & 0xFFFFFF80) == 0) {
149 // will generate one UTF-8 bytes
150 *utf8_output++ = char(word);
151 pos++;
152 } else if ((word & 0xFFFFF800) == 0) {
153 // will generate two UTF-8 bytes
154 // we have 0b110XXXXX 0b10XXXXXX
155 *utf8_output++ = char((word >> 6) | 0b11000000);
156 *utf8_output++ = char((word & 0b111111) | 0b10000000);
157 pos++;
158 } else if ((word & 0xFFFF0000) == 0) {
159 // will generate three UTF-8 bytes
160 // we have 0b1110XXXX 0b10XXXXXX 0b10XXXXXX
161 if (word >= 0xD800 && word <= 0xDFFF) {
162 return 0;
163 }
164 *utf8_output++ = char((word >> 12) | 0b11100000);
165 *utf8_output++ = char(((word >> 6) & 0b111111) | 0b10000000);
166 *utf8_output++ = char((word & 0b111111) | 0b10000000);
167 pos++;
168 } else {
169 // will generate four UTF-8 bytes
170 // we have 0b11110XXX 0b10XXXXXX 0b10XXXXXX
171 // 0b10XXXXXX
172 if (word > 0x10FFFF) {
173 return 0;
174 }
175 *utf8_output++ = char((word >> 18) | 0b11110000);
176 *utf8_output++ = char(((word >> 12) & 0b111111) | 0b10000000);
177 *utf8_output++ = char(((word >> 6) & 0b111111) | 0b10000000);
178 *utf8_output++ = char((word & 0b111111) | 0b10000000);
179 pos++;
180 }
181 }
182 return utf8_output - start;
183}

2639// This can be greatly accelerated. For now we just use a simply
2640// binary search. In practice, you should *not* do that.
2641uint32_t find_range_index(uint32_t key) {
2643 // This could be implemented with std::lower_bound, but we roll our own
2644 // because we want to allow further optimizations in the future.
2646 uint32_t len = std::size(table);
2647 uint32_t low = 0;
2648 uint32_t high = len - 1;
2649 while (low <= high) {
2650 uint32_t middle_index = (low + high) >> 1; // cannot overflow
2651 uint32_t middle_value = table[middle_index][0];
2652 if (middle_value < key) {
2653 low = middle_index + 1;
2654 } else if (middle_value > key) {
2655 high = middle_index - 1;
2656 } else {
2657 return middle_index; // perfect match
2658 }
2659 }
2660 return low == 0 ? 0 : low - 1;
2661}
2662
2663void ascii_map(char* input, size_t length) {
2664 auto broadcast = [](uint8_t v) -> uint64_t {
2665 return 0x101010101010101ull * v;
2666 };
2667 uint64_t broadcast_80 = broadcast(0x80);
2668 uint64_t broadcast_Ap = broadcast(128 - 'A');
2669 uint64_t broadcast_Zp = broadcast(128 - 'Z' - 1);
2670 size_t i = 0;
2671
2672 for (; i + 7 < length; i += 8) {
2673 uint64_t word{};
2674 memcpy(&word, input + i, sizeof(word));
2675 word ^=
2676 (((word + broadcast_Ap) ^ (word + broadcast_Zp)) & broadcast_80) >> 2;
2677 memcpy(input + i, &word, sizeof(word));
2678 }
2679 if (i < length) {
2680 uint64_t word{};
2681 memcpy(&word, input + i, length - i);
2682 word ^=
2683 (((word + broadcast_Ap) ^ (word + broadcast_Zp)) & broadcast_80) >> 2;
2684 memcpy(input + i, &word, length - i);
2685 }
2686}
2687
2688// Map the characters according to IDNA, returning the empty string on error.
2689std::u32string map(std::u32string_view input) {
2690 // [Map](https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr46/#ProcessingStepMap).
2691 // For each code point in the domain_name string, look up the status
2692 // value in Section 5, [IDNA Mapping
2693 // Table](https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr46/#IDNA_Mapping_Table),
2694 // and take the following actions:
2695 // * disallowed: Leave the code point unchanged in the string, and
2696 // record that there was an error.
2697 // * ignored: Remove the code point from the string. This is
2698 // equivalent to mapping the code point to an empty string.
2699 // * mapped: Replace the code point in the string by the value for
2700 // the mapping in Section 5, [IDNA Mapping
2701 // Table](https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr46/#IDNA_Mapping_Table).
2702 // * valid: Leave the code point unchanged in the string.
2703 static std::u32string error = U"";
2704 std::u32string answer;
2705 answer.reserve(input.size());
2706 for (char32_t x : input) {
2707 size_t index = find_range_index(x);
2708 uint32_t descriptor = table[index][1];
2709 uint8_t code = uint8_t(descriptor);
2710 switch (code) {
2711 case 0:
2712 break; // nothing to do, ignored
2713 case 1:
2714 answer.push_back(x); // valid, we just copy it to output
2715 break;
2716 case 2:
2717 return error; // disallowed
2718 // case 3 :
2719 default:
2720 // We have a mapping
2721 {
2722 size_t char_count = (descriptor >> 24);
2723 uint16_t char_index = uint16_t(descriptor >> 8);
2724 for (size_t idx = char_index; idx < char_index + char_count; idx++) {
2725 answer.push_back(mappings[idx]);
2726 }
2727 }
2728 }
2729 }
2730 return answer;
2731}

7636// See
7637// https://github.com/uni-algo/uni-algo/blob/c612968c5ed3ace39bde4c894c24286c5f2c7fe2/include/uni_algo/impl/impl_norm.h#L467
7638constexpr char32_t hangul_sbase = 0xAC00;
7639constexpr char32_t hangul_tbase = 0x11A7;
7640constexpr char32_t hangul_vbase = 0x1161;
7641constexpr char32_t hangul_lbase = 0x1100;
7642constexpr char32_t hangul_lcount = 19;
7643constexpr char32_t hangul_vcount = 21;
7644constexpr char32_t hangul_tcount = 28;
7645constexpr char32_t hangul_ncount = hangul_vcount * hangul_tcount;
7646constexpr char32_t hangul_scount =
7647 hangul_lcount * hangul_vcount * hangul_tcount;
7648
7649std::pair<bool, size_t> compute_decomposition_length(
7650 const std::u32string_view input) noexcept {
7651 bool decomposition_needed{false};
7652 size_t additional_elements{0};
7653 for (char32_t current_character : input) {
7654 size_t decomposition_length{0};
7655
7656 if (current_character >= hangul_sbase &&
7657 current_character < hangul_sbase + hangul_scount) {
7658 decomposition_length = 2;
7659 if ((current_character - hangul_sbase) % hangul_tcount) {
7660 decomposition_length = 3;
7661 }
7662 } else if (current_character < 0x110000) {
7663 const uint8_t di = decomposition_index[current_character >> 8];
7664 const uint16_t* const decomposition =
7665 decomposition_block[di] + (current_character % 256);
7666 decomposition_length = (decomposition[1] >> 2) - (decomposition[0] >> 2);
7667 if ((decomposition_length > 0) && (decomposition[0] & 1)) {
7668 decomposition_length = 0;
7669 }
7670 }
7671 if (decomposition_length != 0) {
7672 decomposition_needed = true;
7673 additional_elements += decomposition_length - 1;
7674 }
7675 }
7676 return {decomposition_needed, additional_elements};
7677}
7678
7679void decompose(std::u32string& input, size_t additional_elements) {
7680 input.resize(input.size() + additional_elements);
7681 for (size_t descending_idx = input.size(),
7682 input_count = descending_idx - additional_elements;
7683 input_count--;) {
7684 if (input[input_count] >= hangul_sbase &&
7685 input[input_count] < hangul_sbase + hangul_scount) {
7686 // Hangul decomposition.
7687 char32_t s_index = input[input_count] - hangul_sbase;
7688 if (s_index % hangul_tcount != 0) {
7689 input[--descending_idx] = hangul_tbase + s_index % hangul_tcount;
7690 }
7691 input[--descending_idx] =
7692 hangul_vbase + (s_index % hangul_ncount) / hangul_tcount;
7693 input[--descending_idx] = hangul_lbase + s_index / hangul_ncount;
7694 } else if (input[input_count] < 0x110000) {
7695 // Check decomposition_data.
7696 const uint16_t* decomposition =
7697 decomposition_block[decomposition_index[input[input_count] >> 8]] +
7698 (input[input_count] % 256);
7699 uint16_t decomposition_length =
7700 (decomposition[1] >> 2) - (decomposition[0] >> 2);
7701 if (decomposition_length > 0 && (decomposition[0] & 1)) {
7702 decomposition_length = 0;
7703 }
7704 if (decomposition_length > 0) {
7705 // Non-recursive decomposition.
7706 while (decomposition_length-- > 0) {
7707 input[--descending_idx] = decomposition_data[(decomposition[0] >> 2) +
7708 decomposition_length];
7709 }
7710 } else {
7711 // No decomposition.
7712 input[--descending_idx] = input[input_count];
7713 }
7714 } else {
7715 // Non-Unicode character.
7716 input[--descending_idx] = input[input_count];
7717 }
7718 }
7719}
7720
7721uint8_t get_ccc(char32_t c) noexcept {
7722 return c < 0x110000 ? canonical_combining_class_block
7723 [canonical_combining_class_index[c >> 8]][c % 256]
7724 : 0;
7725}
7726
7727void sort_marks(std::u32string& input) {
7728 for (size_t idx = 1; idx < input.size(); idx++) {
7729 uint8_t ccc = get_ccc(input[idx]);
7730 if (ccc == 0) {
7731 continue;
7732 } // Skip non-combining characters.
7733 auto current_character = input[idx];
7734 size_t back_idx = idx;
7735 while (back_idx != 0 && get_ccc(input[back_idx - 1]) > ccc) {
7736 input[back_idx] = input[back_idx - 1];
7737 back_idx--;
7738 }
7739 input[back_idx] = current_character;
7740 }
7741}
7742
7743void decompose_nfc(std::u32string& input) {
7748 auto [decomposition_needed, additional_elements] =
7749 compute_decomposition_length(input);
7750 if (decomposition_needed) {
7751 decompose(input, additional_elements);
7752 }
7753 sort_marks(input);
7754}
7755
7756void compose(std::u32string& input) {
7761 size_t input_count{0};
7762 size_t composition_count{0};
7763 for (; input_count < input.size(); input_count++, composition_count++) {
7764 input[composition_count] = input[input_count];
7765 if (input[input_count] >= hangul_lbase &&
7766 input[input_count] < hangul_lbase + hangul_lcount) {
7767 if (input_count + 1 < input.size() &&
7768 input[input_count + 1] >= hangul_vbase &&
7769 input[input_count + 1] < hangul_vbase + hangul_vcount) {
7770 input[composition_count] =
7771 hangul_sbase +
7772 ((input[input_count] - hangul_lbase) * hangul_vcount +
7773 input[input_count + 1] - hangul_vbase) *
7774 hangul_tcount;
7775 input_count++;
7776 if (input_count + 1 < input.size() &&
7777 input[input_count + 1] > hangul_tbase &&
7778 input[input_count + 1] < hangul_tbase + hangul_tcount) {
7779 input[composition_count] += input[++input_count] - hangul_tbase;
7780 }
7781 }
7782 } else if (input[input_count] >= hangul_sbase &&
7783 input[input_count] < hangul_sbase + hangul_scount) {
7784 if ((input[input_count] - hangul_sbase) % hangul_tcount &&
7785 input_count + 1 < input.size() &&
7786 input[input_count + 1] > hangul_tbase &&
7787 input[input_count + 1] < hangul_tbase + hangul_tcount) {
7788 input[composition_count] += input[++input_count] - hangul_tbase;
7789 }
7790 } else if (input[input_count] < 0x110000) {
7791 const uint16_t* composition =
7792 &composition_block[composition_index[input[input_count] >> 8]]
7793 [input[input_count] % 256];
7794 size_t initial_composition_count = composition_count;
7795 for (int32_t previous_ccc = -1; input_count + 1 < input.size();
7796 input_count++) {
7797 uint8_t ccc = get_ccc(input[input_count + 1]);
7798
7799 if (composition[1] != composition[0] && previous_ccc < ccc) {
7800 // Try finding a composition.
7801 int left = composition[0];
7802 int right = composition[1];
7803 while (left + 2 < right) {
7804 // mean without overflow
7805 int middle = left + (((right - left) >> 1) & ~1);
7806 if (composition_data[middle] <= input[input_count + 1]) {
7807 left = middle;
7808 }
7809 if (composition_data[middle] >= input[input_count + 1]) {
7810 right = middle;
7811 }
7812 }
7813 if (composition_data[left] == input[input_count + 1]) {
7814 input[initial_composition_count] = composition_data[left + 1];
7815 composition =
7816 &composition_block
7817 [composition_index[composition_data[left + 1] >> 8]]
7818 [composition_data[left + 1] % 256];
7819 continue;
7820 }
7821 }
7822
7823 if (ccc == 0) {
7824 break;
7825 } // Not a combining character.
7826 previous_ccc = ccc;
7827 input[++composition_count] = input[input_count + 1];
7828 }
7829 }
7830 }
7831
7832 if (composition_count < input_count) {
7833 input.resize(composition_count);
7834 }
7835}
7836
7837void normalize(std::u32string& input) {
7842 decompose_nfc(input);
7843 compose(input);
7844}

7850#include <cstdint>

7853
7854constexpr int32_t base = 36;
7855constexpr int32_t tmin = 1;
7856constexpr int32_t tmax = 26;
7857constexpr int32_t skew = 38;
7858constexpr int32_t damp = 700;
7859constexpr int32_t initial_bias = 72;
7860constexpr uint32_t initial_n = 128;
7861
7862static constexpr int32_t char_to_digit_value(char value) {
7863 if (value >= 'a' && value <= 'z') return value - 'a';
7864 if (value >= '0' && value <= '9') return value - '0' + 26;
7865 return -1;
7866}
7867
7868static constexpr char digit_to_char(int32_t digit) {
7869 return digit < 26 ? char(digit + 97) : char(digit + 22);
7870}
7871
7872static constexpr int32_t adapt(int32_t d, int32_t n, bool firsttime) {
7873 if (firsttime) {
7874 d = d / damp;
7875 } else {
7876 d = d / 2;
7877 }
7878 d += d / n;
7879 int32_t k = 0;
7880 while (d > ((base - tmin) * tmax) / 2) {
7881 d /= base - tmin;
7882 k += base;
7883 }
7884 return k + (((base - tmin + 1) * d) / (d + skew));
7885}
7886
7887bool punycode_to_utf32(std::string_view input, std::u32string &out) {
7888 // See https://github.com/whatwg/url/issues/803
7889 if (input.starts_with("xn--")) {
7890 return false;
7891 }
7892 int32_t written_out{0};
7893 out.reserve(out.size() + input.size());
7894 uint32_t n = initial_n;
7895 int32_t i = 0;
7896 int32_t bias = initial_bias;
7897 // grab ascii content
7898 size_t end_of_ascii = input.find_last_of('-');
7899 if (end_of_ascii != std::string_view::npos) {
7900 for (uint8_t c : input.substr(0, end_of_ascii)) {
7901 if (c >= 0x80) {
7902 return false;
7903 }
7904 out.push_back(c);
7905 written_out++;
7906 }
7907 input.remove_prefix(end_of_ascii + 1);
7908 }
7909 while (!input.empty()) {
7910 int32_t oldi = i;
7911 int32_t w = 1;
7912 for (int32_t k = base;; k += base) {
7913 if (input.empty()) {
7914 return false;
7915 }
7916 uint8_t code_point = input.front();
7917 input.remove_prefix(1);
7918 int32_t digit = char_to_digit_value(code_point);
7919 if (digit < 0) {
7920 return false;
7921 }
7922 if (digit > (0x7fffffff - i) / w) {
7923 return false;
7924 }
7925 i = i + digit * w;
7926 int32_t t = k <= bias ? tmin : k >= bias + tmax ? tmax : k - bias;
7927 if (digit < t) {
7928 break;
7929 }
7930 if (w > 0x7fffffff / (base - t)) {
7931 return false;
7932 }
7933 w = w * (base - t);
7934 }
7935 bias = adapt(i - oldi, written_out + 1, oldi == 0);
7936 if (i / (written_out + 1) > int32_t(0x7fffffff - n)) {
7937 return false;
7938 }
7939 n = n + i / (written_out + 1);
7940 i = i % (written_out + 1);
7941 if (n < 0x80) {
7942 return false;
7943 }
7944 out.insert(out.begin() + i, n);
7945 written_out++;
7946 ++i;
7947 }
7948 return true;
7949}
7950
7951bool verify_punycode(std::string_view input) {
7952 if (input.starts_with("xn--")) {
7953 return false;
7954 }
7955 size_t written_out{0};
7956 uint32_t n = initial_n;
7957 int32_t i = 0;
7958 int32_t bias = initial_bias;
7959 // grab ascii content
7960 size_t end_of_ascii = input.find_last_of('-');
7961 if (end_of_ascii != std::string_view::npos) {
7962 for (uint8_t c : input.substr(0, end_of_ascii)) {
7963 if (c >= 0x80) {
7964 return false;
7965 }
7966 written_out++;
7967 }
7968 input.remove_prefix(end_of_ascii + 1);
7969 }
7970 while (!input.empty()) {
7971 int32_t oldi = i;
7972 int32_t w = 1;
7973 for (int32_t k = base;; k += base) {
7974 if (input.empty()) {
7975 return false;
7976 }
7977 uint8_t code_point = input.front();
7978 input.remove_prefix(1);
7979 int32_t digit = char_to_digit_value(code_point);
7980 if (digit < 0) {
7981 return false;
7982 }
7983 if (digit > (0x7fffffff - i) / w) {
7984 return false;
7985 }
7986 i = i + digit * w;
7987 int32_t t = k <= bias ? tmin : k >= bias + tmax ? tmax : k - bias;
7988 if (digit < t) {
7989 break;
7990 }
7991 if (w > 0x7fffffff / (base - t)) {
7992 return false;
7993 }
7994 w = w * (base - t);
7995 }
7996 bias = adapt(i - oldi, int32_t(written_out + 1), oldi == 0);
7997 if (i / (written_out + 1) > 0x7fffffff - n) {
7998 return false;
7999 }
8000 n = n + i / int32_t(written_out + 1);
8001 i = i % int32_t(written_out + 1);
8002 if (n < 0x80) {
8003 return false;
8004 }
8005 written_out++;
8006 ++i;
8007 }
8008
8009 return true;
8010}
8011
8012bool utf32_to_punycode(std::u32string_view input, std::string &out) {
8013 out.reserve(input.size() + out.size());
8014 uint32_t n = initial_n;
8015 int32_t d = 0;
8016 int32_t bias = initial_bias;
8017 size_t h = 0;
8018 // first push the ascii content
8019 for (uint32_t c : input) {
8020 if (c < 0x80) {
8021 ++h;
8022 out.push_back(char(c));
8023 }
8024 if (c > 0x10ffff || (c >= 0xd880 && c < 0xe000)) {
8025 return false;
8026 }
8027 }
8028 size_t b = h;
8029 if (b > 0) {
8030 out.push_back('-');
8031 }
8032 while (h < input.size()) {
8033 uint32_t m = 0x10FFFF;
8034 for (auto code_point : input) {
8035 if (code_point >= n && code_point < m) m = code_point;
8036 }
8037
8038 if ((m - n) > (0x7fffffff - d) / (h + 1)) {
8039 return false;
8040 }
8041 d = d + int32_t((m - n) * (h + 1));
8042 n = m;
8043 for (auto c : input) {
8044 if (c < n) {
8045 if (d == 0x7fffffff) {
8046 return false;
8047 }
8048 ++d;
8049 }
8050 if (c == n) {
8051 int32_t q = d;
8052 for (int32_t k = base;; k += base) {
8053 int32_t t = k <= bias ? tmin : k >= bias + tmax ? tmax : k - bias;
8054
8055 if (q < t) {
8056 break;
8057 }
8058 out.push_back(digit_to_char(t + ((q - t) % (base - t))));
8059 q = (q - t) / (base - t);
8060 }
8061 out.push_back(digit_to_char(q));
8062 bias = adapt(d, int32_t(h + 1), h == b);
8063 d = 0;
8064 ++h;
8065 }
8066 }
8067 ++d;
8068 ++n;
8069 }
8070 return true;
8071}
8072
8073} // namespace ada::idna
8074/* end file src/punycode.cpp */

8840
8841// CheckJoiners and CheckBidi are true for URL specification.
8842
8843inline static direction find_direction(uint32_t code_point) noexcept {
8844 auto it = std::lower_bound(
8845 std::begin(dir_table), std::end(dir_table), code_point,
8846 [](const directions& d, uint32_t c) { return d.final_code < c; });
8847
8848 // next check is almost surely in vain, but we use it for safety.
8849 if (it == std::end(dir_table)) {
8850 return direction::NONE;
8851 }
8852 // We have that d.final_code >= c.
8853 if (code_point >= it->start_code) {
8854 return it->direct;
8855 }
8856 return direction::NONE;
8857}
8858
8859inline static size_t find_last_not_of_nsm(
8860 const std::u32string_view label) noexcept {
8861 for (int i = static_cast<int>(label.size() - 1); i >= 0; i--)
8862 if (find_direction(label[i]) != direction::NSM) return i;
8863
8864 return std::u32string_view::npos;
8865}
8866
8867// An RTL label is a label that contains at least one character of type R, AL,
8868// or AN. https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc5893#section-2
8869inline static bool is_rtl_label(const std::u32string_view label) noexcept {
8870 const size_t mask =
8871 (1u << direction::R) | (1u << direction::AL) | (1u << direction::AN);
8872
8873 size_t directions = 0;
8874 for (size_t i = 0; i < label.size(); i++) {
8875 directions |= 1u << find_direction(label[i]);
8876 }
8877 return (directions & mask) != 0;
8878}

8881 if (label.empty()) {
8882 return true;

8888 // version matches the original.

9267 for (size_t i = 0; i < label.size(); i++) {
9268 uint32_t c = label[i];
9269 if (c == 0x200c) {
9270 if (i > 0) {
9271 if (std::binary_search(std::begin(virama), std::end(virama),
9272 label[i - 1])) {
9273 return true;
9274 }
9275 }
9276 if ((i == 0) || (i + 1 >= label.size())) {
9277 return false;
9278 }
9279 // we go backward looking for L or D
9280 auto is_l_or_d = [](uint32_t code) {
9281 return std::binary_search(std::begin(L), std::end(L), code) ||
9282 std::binary_search(std::begin(D), std::end(D), code);
9283 };
9284 auto is_r_or_d = [](uint32_t code) {
9285 return std::binary_search(std::begin(R), std::end(R), code) ||
9286 std::binary_search(std::begin(D), std::end(D), code);
9287 };
9288 std::u32string_view before = label.substr(0, i);
9289 std::u32string_view after = label.substr(i + 1);
9290 return (std::find_if(before.begin(), before.end(), is_l_or_d) !=
9291 before.end()) &&
9292 (std::find_if(after.begin(), after.end(), is_r_or_d) !=
9293 after.end());
9294 } else if (c == 0x200d) {
9295 if (i > 0) {
9296 if (std::binary_search(std::begin(virama), std::end(virama),
9297 label[i - 1])) {
9298 return true;
9299 }
9300 }
9301 return false;
9302 }
9303 }
9304
9305 // If CheckBidi, and if the domain name is a Bidi domain name, then the label
9306 // must satisfy all six of the numbered conditions in [IDNA2008] RFC 5893,
9307 // Section 2.
9308
9309 // The following rule, consisting of six conditions, applies to labels
9310 // in Bidi domain names. The requirements that this rule satisfies are
9311 // described in Section 3. All of the conditions must be satisfied for
9312 // the rule to be satisfied.
9313 //
9314 // 1. The first character must be a character with Bidi property L, R,
9315 // or AL. If it has the R or AL property, it is an RTL label; if it
9316 // has the L property, it is an LTR label.
9317 //
9318 // 2. In an RTL label, only characters with the Bidi properties R, AL,
9319 // AN, EN, ES, CS, ET, ON, BN, or NSM are allowed.
9320 //
9321 // 3. In an RTL label, the end of the label must be a character with
9322 // Bidi property R, AL, EN, or AN, followed by zero or more
9323 // characters with Bidi property NSM.
9324 //
9325 // 4. In an RTL label, if an EN is present, no AN may be present, and
9326 // vice versa.
9327 //
9328 // 5. In an LTR label, only characters with the Bidi properties L, EN,
9329 // ES, CS, ET, ON, BN, or NSM are allowed.
9330 //
9331 // 6. In an LTR label, the end of the label must be a character with
9332 // Bidi property L or EN, followed by zero or more characters with
9333 // Bidi property NSM.
9334
9335 size_t last_non_nsm_char = find_last_not_of_nsm(label);
9336 if (last_non_nsm_char == std::u32string_view::npos) {
9337 return false;
9338 }
9339
9340 // A "Bidi domain name" is a domain name that contains at least one RTL label.
9341 // The following rule, consisting of six conditions, applies to labels in Bidi
9342 // domain names.
9343 if (is_rtl_label(label)) {
9344 // The first character must be a character with Bidi property L, R,
9345 // or AL. If it has the R or AL property, it is an RTL label; if it
9346 // has the L property, it is an LTR label.
9347
9348 if (find_direction(label[0]) == direction::L) {
9349 // Eval as LTR
9350
9351 // In an LTR label, only characters with the Bidi properties L, EN,
9352 // ES, CS, ET, ON, BN, or NSM are allowed.
9353 for (size_t i = 0; i < last_non_nsm_char; i++) {
9354 const direction d = find_direction(label[i]);
9355 if (!(d == direction::L || d == direction::EN || d == direction::ES ||
9356 d == direction::CS || d == direction::ET || d == direction::ON ||
9357 d == direction::BN || d == direction::NSM)) {
9358 return false;
9359 }
9360
9361 if ((i == last_non_nsm_char) &&
9362 !(d == direction::L || d == direction::EN)) {
9363 return false;
9364 }
9365 }
9366
9367 return true;
9368
9369 } else {
9370 // Eval as RTL
9371
9372 bool has_an = false;
9373 bool has_en = false;
9374 for (size_t i = 0; i <= last_non_nsm_char; i++) {
9375 const direction d = find_direction(label[i]);
9376
9377 // In an RTL label, if an EN is present, no AN may be present, and vice
9378 // versa.
9379 if ((d == direction::EN && ((has_en = true) && has_an)) ||
9380 (d == direction::AN && ((has_an = true) && has_en))) {
9381 return false;
9382 }
9383
9384 if (!(d == direction::R || d == direction::AL || d == direction::AN ||
9385 d == direction::EN || d == direction::ES || d == direction::CS ||
9386 d == direction::ET || d == direction::ON || d == direction::BN ||
9387 d == direction::NSM)) {
9388 return false;
9389 }
9390
9391 if (i == last_non_nsm_char &&
9392 !(d == direction::R || d == direction::AL || d == direction::AN ||
9393 d == direction::EN)) {
9394 return false;
9395 }
9396 }
9397
9398 return true;
9399 }
9400 }
9401
9402 return true;
9403}

9457// We return "" on error.
9458static std::string from_ascii_to_ascii(std::string_view ut8_string) {
9459 static const std::string error = "";
9460 // copy and map
9461 // we could be more efficient by avoiding the copy when unnecessary.
9462 std::string mapped_string = std::string(ut8_string);
9463 ascii_map(mapped_string.data(), mapped_string.size());
9464 std::string out;
9465 size_t label_start = 0;
9466
9467 while (label_start != mapped_string.size()) {
9468 size_t loc_dot = mapped_string.find('.', label_start);
9469 bool is_last_label = (loc_dot == std::string_view::npos);
9470 size_t label_size = is_last_label ? mapped_string.size() - label_start
9471 : loc_dot - label_start;
9472 size_t label_size_with_dot = is_last_label ? label_size : label_size + 1;
9473 std::string_view label_view(mapped_string.data() + label_start, label_size);
9474 label_start += label_size_with_dot;
9475 if (label_size == 0) {
9476 // empty label? Nothing to do.
9477 } else if (label_view.starts_with("xn--")) {
9478 // The xn-- part is the expensive game.
9479 out.append(label_view);
9480 std::string_view puny_segment_ascii(
9481 out.data() + out.size() - label_view.size() + 4,
9482 label_view.size() - 4);
9483 std::u32string tmp_buffer;
9484 bool is_ok = ada::idna::punycode_to_utf32(puny_segment_ascii, tmp_buffer);
9485 if (!is_ok) {
9486 return error;
9487 }
9488 // If the input is just ASCII, it should not have been encoded
9489 // as punycode.
9490 // https://github.com/whatwg/url/issues/760
9491 if (is_ascii(tmp_buffer)) {
9492 return error;
9493 }
9494 std::u32string post_map = ada::idna::map(tmp_buffer);
9495 if (tmp_buffer != post_map) {
9496 return error;
9497 }
9498 std::u32string pre_normal = post_map;
9499 normalize(post_map);
9500 if (post_map != pre_normal) {
9501 return error;
9502 }
9503 if (post_map.empty()) {
9504 return error;
9505 }
9506 if (!is_label_valid(post_map)) {
9507 return error;
9508 }
9509 } else {
9510 out.append(label_view);
9511 }
9512 if (!is_last_label) {
9513 out.push_back('.');
9514 }
9515 }
9516 return out;
9517}
9518
9519// We return "" on error.
9520std::string to_ascii(std::string_view ut8_string) {
9521 if (is_ascii(ut8_string)) {
9522 return from_ascii_to_ascii(ut8_string);
9523 }
9524 static const std::string error = "";
9525 // We convert to UTF-32
9526 size_t utf32_length =
9527 ada::idna::utf32_length_from_utf8(ut8_string.data(), ut8_string.size());
9528 std::u32string utf32(utf32_length, '\0');
9529 size_t actual_utf32_length = ada::idna::utf8_to_utf32(
9530 ut8_string.data(), ut8_string.size(), utf32.data());
9531 if (actual_utf32_length == 0) {
9532 return error;
9533 }
9534 // mapping
9535 utf32 = ada::idna::map(utf32);
9536 normalize(utf32);
9537 std::string out;
9538 size_t label_start = 0;
9539
9540 while (label_start != utf32.size()) {
9541 size_t loc_dot = utf32.find('.', label_start);
9542 bool is_last_label = (loc_dot == std::string_view::npos);
9543 size_t label_size =
9544 is_last_label ? utf32.size() - label_start : loc_dot - label_start;
9545 size_t label_size_with_dot = is_last_label ? label_size : label_size + 1;
9546 std::u32string_view label_view(utf32.data() + label_start, label_size);
9547 label_start += label_size_with_dot;
9548 if (label_size == 0) {
9549 // empty label? Nothing to do.
9550 } else if (label_view.starts_with(U"xn--")) {
9551 // we do not need to check, e.g., Xn-- because mapping goes to lower case
9552 for (char32_t c : label_view) {
9553 if (c >= 0x80) {
9554 return error;
9555 }
9556 out += (unsigned char)(c);
9557 }
9558 std::string_view puny_segment_ascii(
9559 out.data() + out.size() - label_view.size() + 4,
9560 label_view.size() - 4);
9561 std::u32string tmp_buffer;
9562 bool is_ok = ada::idna::punycode_to_utf32(puny_segment_ascii, tmp_buffer);
9563 if (!is_ok) {
9564 return error;
9565 }
9566 // If the input is just ASCII, it should not have been encoded
9567 // as punycode.
9568 // https://github.com/whatwg/url/issues/760
9569 if (is_ascii(tmp_buffer)) {
9570 return error;
9571 }
9572 std::u32string post_map = ada::idna::map(tmp_buffer);
9573 if (tmp_buffer != post_map) {
9574 return error;
9575 }
9576 std::u32string pre_normal = post_map;
9577 normalize(post_map);
9578 if (post_map != pre_normal) {
9579 return error;
9580 }
9581 if (post_map.empty()) {
9582 return error;
9583 }
9584 if (!is_label_valid(post_map)) {
9585 return error;
9586 }
9587 } else {
9588 // The fast path here is an ascii label.
9589 if (is_ascii(label_view)) {
9590 // no validation needed.
9591 for (char32_t c : label_view) {
9592 out += (unsigned char)(c);
9593 }
9594 } else {
9595 // slow path.
9596 // first check validity.
9597 if (!is_label_valid(label_view)) {
9598 return error;
9599 }
9600 // It is valid! So now we must encode it as punycode...
9601 out.append("xn--");
9602 bool is_ok = ada::idna::utf32_to_punycode(label_view, out);
9603 if (!is_ok) {
9604 return error;
9605 }
9606 }
9607 }
9608 if (!is_last_label) {
9609 out.push_back('.');
9610 }
9611 }
9612 return out;
9613}
9614} // namespace ada::idna
9615/* end file src/to_ascii.cpp */
9616/* begin file src/to_unicode.cpp */
9617
9618#include <algorithm>
9619#include <string>
9620
9621
9622namespace ada::idna {
9623std::string to_unicode(std::string_view input) {
9624 std::string output;
9625 output.reserve(input.size());
9626
9627 size_t label_start = 0;
9628 while (label_start < input.size()) {
9629 size_t loc_dot = input.find('.', label_start);
9630 bool is_last_label = (loc_dot == std::string_view::npos);
9631 size_t label_size =
9632 is_last_label ? input.size() - label_start : loc_dot - label_start;
9633 auto label_view = std::string_view(input.data() + label_start, label_size);
9634
9635 if (label_view.starts_with("xn--") && ada::idna::is_ascii(label_view)) {
9636 label_view.remove_prefix(4);
9637 if (ada::idna::verify_punycode(label_view)) {
9638 std::u32string tmp_buffer;
9639 if (ada::idna::punycode_to_utf32(label_view, tmp_buffer)) {
9640 auto utf8_size = ada::idna::utf8_length_from_utf32(tmp_buffer.data(),
9641 tmp_buffer.size());
9642 std::string final_utf8(utf8_size, '\0');
9643 ada::idna::utf32_to_utf8(tmp_buffer.data(), tmp_buffer.size(),
9644 final_utf8.data());
9645 output.append(final_utf8);
9646 } else {
9647 // ToUnicode never fails. If any step fails, then the original input
9648 // sequence is returned immediately in that step.
9649 output.append(
9650 std::string_view(input.data() + label_start, label_size));
9651 }
9652 } else {
9653 output.append(std::string_view(input.data() + label_start, label_size));
9654 }
9655 } else {
9656 output.append(label_view);
9657 }
9658
9659 if (!is_last_label) {
9660 output.push_back('.');
9661 }
9662
9663 label_start += label_size + 1;
9664 }
9665
9666 return output;
9667}
9668} // namespace ada::idna

10238namespace ada::idna {
10239constexpr bool is_ascii_letter(char32_t c) noexcept {
10240 return (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z');
10241}
10242
10243constexpr bool is_ascii_letter_or_digit(char32_t c) noexcept {
10244 return (c >= 'A' && c <= 'Z') || (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') ||
10245 (c >= '0' && c <= '9');
10246}
10247
10248bool valid_name_code_point(char32_t code_point, bool first) {
10249 // https://tc39.es/ecma262/#prod-IdentifierStart
10250 // Fast paths:
10251 if (first &&
10252 (code_point == '$' || code_point == '_' || is_ascii_letter(code_point))) {
10253 return true;
10254 }
10255 if (!first && (code_point == '$' || is_ascii_letter_or_digit(code_point))) {
10256 return true;
10257 }
10258 // Slow path...
10259 if (code_point == 0xffffffff) {
10260 return false; // minimal error handling
10261 }
10262 if (first) {
10263 auto iter = std::lower_bound(
10264 std::begin(ada::idna::id_start), std::end(ada::idna::id_start),
10265 code_point,
10266 [](const uint32_t* range, uint32_t cp) { return range[1] < cp; });
10267 return iter != std::end(id_start) && code_point >= (*iter)[0];
10268 } else {
10269 auto iter = std::lower_bound(
10270 std::begin(id_continue), std::end(id_continue), code_point,
10271 [](const uint32_t* range, uint32_t cp) { return range[1] < cp; });
10272 return iter != std::end(id_start) && code_point >= (*iter)[0];
10273 }
10274}
10275} // namespace ada::idna
